      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">RogueWatchmen wrote:</div><div class="orig">So I'm rank 18 GLA, but in all honesty since I picked up MAR I really dont play it outside GLA levi's, I notice there are skills that look cross class like Mind over Matter etc, but I dont really understand how they operate. For example Mind of Matter is Converts an attribute point allocation of Dexterity +5 into Mind +5. Does that mean that 6 points of Dex are lost to Mind which gains 6 points? Without knowing this I cant decide what to buy first. Any suggestions? BTW I picked that skill at random so it wasn't a consideration or anyhting lol.</div></div> <br /> <br />These are more traits for allowing you to swap classes easier. Imagine playing a high ranked gladiator with all your points in STR/VIT/DEX. You can set these traits you learn and it will move some of your points around. I suggest getting Heavy Slash or Self Preservation first for this reason if you intend to main gladiator. I believe you have to be r21 or r22 to get SElf Preservation though.</div>
